summary:
* Welcomes the Optional Protocol to the Convention on the Safety of United Nations and Associated Personnel, adopted by the General Assembly on 8 December 2005, and calls for prosecution or extradition of those responsible;
* Recognizes the valuable role of regional organizations in protecting civilians and encourages strengthened partnerships;
* Invites the Secretary-General to refer relevant information on civilian protection to the Council and to include observations on the issue in his reports;
* Notes that deliberate targeting of civilians and systematic violations of humanitarian and human rights law may constitute a threat to international peace and security and reaffirms its readiness to consider such situations;
* Requests the Secretary-General to submit his next report on protecting civilians in armed conflict within 18 months;
* Decides to remain seized of the matter.
